<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="210" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d210">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName></hi>,</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation at Bogotá</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-10-31"><hi rend="italic">October
                                        31, 1903</hi></date>. (Received November 6,
                                1903.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Congress adjourned to-day. No action has been taken upon the last report
                            concerning the canal. Therefore nothing more than the vote of August 12
                            rejecting treaty done.</p>
                        <p>The people here in great anxiety over conflicting reports of secession
                            movements in the Cauca and Panama.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>